{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Bharath Sriraman | image = | caption = Sriraman, Universidad Antonio Narino, 2015 | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1971}} | birth_place = [[Bangalore|Bangalore, India]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[United States|American]] | fields = [[mathematics education]], [[creativity]], [[alternative education]], [[gifted education]] | workplaces = [[University of Montana – Missoula|The University of Montana]] | alma_mater = [[University of Alaska Fairbanks]], [[Northern Illinois University]] | doctoral_advisor = Robert Wheeler | awards = 2002 NAGC Distinguished Brief of the Year; SSMA 2007 Early Scholar; 2009 NIU Golden Alumni; 2016 UM Distinguished Scholar }} '''Bharath Sriraman''' (born 1971) is an Indian-born mathematician, educator and academic editor,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.umt.edu/urelations/report/2008/BharathSriraman.html |title=The University of Montana 2008 President's Report |publisher=Umt.edu |date= |accessdate=2010-07-25}}</ref> known for his interdisciplinary contributions at the nexus of math-science-arts,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://research.blog.umt.edu/post/83745161018/um-professor-interviewed-for-roeper-review|title=UM Professor Interviewed for Roeper Review |publisher=Umt.edu |date= |accessdate=2014-11-10}}</ref> theory development in mathematics education, [[creativity]] research,<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.kaputcenter.umassd.edu/events/symposia/sriraman_symposium/|title=Symposium: Mathematical Creativity- Musings from the Past Decade |publisher=Kaputcenter.umass.edu |date= |accessdate=2017-01-14}}</ref> and alternative education.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://gazette.jhu.edu/2011/03/21/cty-math-minds-and-a-milestone/ |title=Study of Mathematically Precocious Youth 40th Anniversary Symposium|publisher=Johns Hopkins University |date= |accessdate=2012-04-04}}</ref>
== Academic and editorial work == Bharath Sriraman is a professor of mathematics at the [[University of Montana – Missoula]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hs.umt.edu/math/people/faculty-details.php?id=667 |title=CAS &#124; Faculty Details |publisher=Cas.umt.edu |date=2007-06-08 |accessdate=2016-01-14}}</ref> with an adjunct appointment in the department of Central and Southwest-Asian Studies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hs.umt.edu/cswa/people/default.php|title=Central and Southwest Asia Program (CAP) |publisher=Umt.edu |date= |accessdate=2016-09-09}}</ref> Sriraman is the founder and [[editor-in-chief]] of ''[[The Mathematics Enthusiast]]'', an independent [[open access journal]] hosted by University of Montana.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scholarworks.umt.edu/tme/ |title= The Mathematics Enthusiast|date=|accessdate=2015-05-27}}</ref> He is the co-founder/co-editor-in-chief of two series with [[Springer Science+Business Media]] namely ''[[Advances in Mathematics Education]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.springer.com/series/8392|title=Advances in Mathematics Education, Springer Heidelberg|publisher=springer.com |accessdate=2016-01-14}}</ref> and ''[[Creativity Theory and Action in Education]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.springer.com/series/13904|title=Creativity Theory and Action in Education, Springer Switzerland|publisher=springer.com |accessdate=2016-01-14}}</ref> He is also the series editor for a number of book series on alternative education published by [[Sense Publishers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sensepublishers.com/catalogs/bookseries/advances-in-creativity-and-giftedness/|title=Advances in Creativity and Giftedness, Sense Publishers|publisher=Sensepublishers.com |accessdate=2012-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sensepublishers.com/catalogs/bookseries/advances-in-innovation-education/|title=Advances in Innovation Education, Sense Publishers|publisher=Sensepublishers.com |accessdate=2015-05-25}}</ref> and various topics in mathematics education with [[Information Age Publishing]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infoagepub.com/authors/bharath-sriraman|title=IAP Author and Editor |publisher=infoagepub.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-04}}</ref> In addition to editing he is a prolific scholar with over 300 publications to date in numerous areas of research,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=YnPG9YoAAAAJ&hl=en|title= Google Scholar Papers|date=|accessdate=2016-09-09}}</ref> and held numerous visiting professorships including those as International Fulbright Specialist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uan.edu.co/noticias?option=com_content&view=article&id=1449:la-uan-recibio-la-grata-visita-del-dr-bharath-sriraman&catid=29&Itemid=1737|title=UAN Fulbright Visit of Dr.Bharath Sriraman |accessdate=2016-12-26}}</ref> at institutions in Nordic countries,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hi.is/vidburdir/vinnustofa_um_skapandi_staerdfraedi|title=University of Iceland: Workshop on Creative Mathematics |accessdate=2016-03-13}}</ref> Eurasia and South America <ref>{{cite web|url=http://visiondemujerperonista.com/2012/?p=3995|title=Conceptualmente la Matemática es más un arte que una ciencia |accessdate=2016-03-04}}</ref>
==Education and honors== Bharath Sriraman graduated with a [[Bachelor of Science|B.S.]] in mathematics from the [[University of Alaska Fairbanks]] in 1995<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.uaf.edu/alumnus-7/2/|title =Class Notes|publisher=Aurora Alumni magazine|date= |accessdate=2010-07-27}}</ref> and obtained his [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in mathematical sciences in 2002 from [[Northern Illinois University]] under the analyst Robert Wheeler.<ref>{{MathGenealogy|id=3564|name=Robert Wheeler}}</ref> In 2009, Northern Illinois University named him as one of 50 "Golden alumni" in the last 50 years for his significant contributions to research in mathematics education, gifted education and interdisciplinary research at the intersection of mathematics-science-arts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://niu.edu/clas50/50alumni/sriraman.shtml |title=Bharath R. Sriraman &ndash; NIU &ndash; LA&S 50th Anniversary |publisher=Niu.edu |date= |accessdate=2010-07-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007045214/http://niu.edu/clas50/50alumni/sriraman.shtml |archivedate=7 October 2013 }}</ref> He previously received the School Science and Mathematics Association Early Scholar Award in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssma.org/past-recipients |title=SSMA Past Award Recipients |publisher=www.ssma.org |date= |accessdate=2010-07-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130714163934/http://www.ssma.org/past-recipients |archivedate=14 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> In 2016 he was the recipient of the University of Montana Distinguished Scholar Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.umt.edu/2016/04/041916umrd.php|title=2016 UM Employee Day|publisher=www.umt.edu |accessdate=2016-08-09}}</ref>
