==Vowels==
Dutch has an extensive [[vowel]] inventory consisting of thirteen plain vowels and at least three diphthongs. Vowels can be grouped as front unrounded, front rounded, central and back. They are also traditionally distinguished by [[Vowel length|length]] or [[tenseness]]. The vowels {{IPA|/eː, øː, oː/}} are included in one of the diphthong charts further below because Northern SD realizes them as diphthongs, but they behave phonologically like the other long monophthongs.

===Monophthongs===
[[Image:Dutch monophthongs chart.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Monophthong]]s of Northern SD, from {{Harvcoltxt|Gussenhoven|1999|p=76}}]]
[[Image:Belgian Dutch monophthongs chart.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Monophthongs of Belgian SD, from {{Harvcoltxt|Verhoeven|2005|p=245}}. The schwa {{IPA|/ə/}} is not shown.]]
[[Image:Dutch allophones of unrounded monophthongs.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Dutch allophones of unrounded monophthongs, from {{Harvcoltxt|Collins|Mees|2003|pp=92, 130, 132, 134}}. Black vowels occur before {{IPA|/r/}} in Northern SD and Randstad Dutch, and the red vowel occurs before the dark {{IPA|/l/}}.{{sfnp|Collins|Mees|2003|pp=92, 130, 132, 234}}]]
[[Image:Dutch allophones of rounded monophthongs.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Dutch allophones of rounded monophthongs, from {{Harvcoltxt|Collins|Mees|2003|pp=98, 130, 132, 134}}. Black vowels occur before {{IPA|/r/}} in Northern SD and Randstad Dutch, and the blue vowel occurs before {{IPA|/ŋ/}}.{{sfnp|Collins|Mees|2003|pp=98, 130, 132, 234}}]]

